      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Grid convergence index (GCI) methodology applied across three systematically refined meshes (3.2M, 8.1M, and 18.7M cells) for the FDA benchmark pump geometry. GCI for NIH predictions: 4.2% on the fine mesh. GCI for pump head: 2.8%. Both below the 5% acceptance threshold for MRL 5.",
